rows.label: tev001091_MSG0001
rows.name: Oh. Hello, [ST:playername ].[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0002
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_JNK0010
rows.name: Inquire

rows.label: tev001091_SEL0011
rows.name: Ask Phog what he's doing.

rows.label: tev001091_JNK0020
rows.name: Speculate

rows.label: tev001091_SEL0021
rows.name: Ask Phog if he's looking at fish.

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0006
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0009
rows.name: Unfortunately, there aren't any fish.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0010
rows.name:
If there were, we could fish here anytime.
That would be nice.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0011
rows.name: ...So I'm thinking about something.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0012
rows.name:
This looks like water, but it's actually a gel designed to
cushion impacts.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0013
rows.name:
I've heard that when it hardens, it becomes like those
giant crystals that surround the outer walls of New LA.
I'm not sure I believe that.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0014
rows.name:
There's a rumor that you could inject a coagulating
agent into it that would cause it to instantly harden...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0015
rows.name:
I was just internally debating whether or not I should
test that theory out.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_JNK0030
rows.name: Encourage

rows.label: tev001091_SEL0031
rows.name: Say you'd also like to know, so Phog should try it.

rows.label: tev001091_JNK0040
rows.name: Discourage

rows.label: tev001091_SEL0041
rows.name:
Explain to Phog how he'd probably
get in trouble for that.

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0016
rows.name: I thought the matter might intrigue you.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0017
rows.name: Please, go ahead and test it out yourself.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0018
rows.name:
I'm going to watch.
...From far away.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0019
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0023
rows.name:
You're not going to do it, are you?
Figures.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0024
rows.name:
If you had, I'm sure Director General Chausson,
Secretary Nagi, and Commander Vandham would
have come down on you like a ton of bricks.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0025
rows.name:
Risking one's life and career to satisfy an idle curiosity
would not be the wisest choice.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0026
rows.name: So I guess we'll resist the temptation to try it for now.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0027
rows.name:
But let's get to the bottom of this on some other day,
and at some other place![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0028
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0029
rows.name:
Yes, that's a fair point.
I should probably hold off.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0030
rows.name:
After all, I've slipped and fallen from the residential
district and landed in this gel more than once...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0031
rows.name:
The gel cushioned my fall, preventing any injuries.
But if it had been crystallized, I could have broken
a leg. Or even two.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0032
rows.name: ......[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0033
rows.name:
I've made up my mind.
I'll leave the gel alone.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev001091_MSG0034
rows.name:
Thankfully, you were here to help me reach the correct
decision![ST:wait ]
